        id: 'codex-adv-3', slug: 'web-search-multimodal', moduleSlug: 'advanced', toolSlug: 'codex',
        title: 'Web Search & Multimodal Input', description: 'Use web search for up-to-date info and attach screenshots for visual context.',
        order: 3, xpReward: 70, estimatedMinutes: 14,
        content: [
          { type: 'markdown', content: '# Web Search & Multimodal Input\n\n## Web Search\n\nCodex ships with a first-party web search tool that lets it look up documentation, error messages, and current information while coding.\n\n### Search Modes\n\n| Mode | Behavior |\n|---|---|\n| **Cached** (default) | Uses an OpenAI-maintained index — faster, safer from prompt injection |\n| **Live** | Fetches the most recent data from the web |\n| **Disabled** | No web search available |' },
          { type: 'code', language: 'bash', code: '# Use live web search for current info\ncodex --search live\n\n# Or set in config\n# ~/.codex/config.toml\n# web_search = "live"', filename: 'terminal' },
          { type: 'markdown', content: '## Multimodal Input\n\nCodex can read screenshots and design specs alongside your prompts. This is powerful for:\n\n- **Debugging visual bugs**: attach a screenshot of the broken UI\n- **Implementing designs**: attach a Figma export or mockup\n- **Error screenshots**: show Codex exactly what you see' },
          { type: 'code', language: 'bash', code: '# Attach a screenshot to your prompt\ncodex -i screenshot.png "Fix the layout issue shown here"\n\n# Attach multiple images\ncodex --image mockup.png,current.png "Make the current page match the mockup"\n\n# Attach a design spec\ncodex -i figma-export.png "Implement this component in React with Tailwind"', filename: 'terminal' },
          { type: 'markdown', content: '## Practical Use Cases\n\n### 1. Debug a Visual Bug\n```\ncodex -i broken-layout.png "The sidebar should be fixed, not overlapping the main content. Fix the CSS."\n```\n\n### 2. Implement from Design\n```\ncodex -i design.png "Create a React component that matches this design. Use Tailwind CSS and make it responsive."\n```\n\n### 3. Look Up Current Docs\n```\n"What is the latest Next.js App Router pattern for loading states? Search the docs."\n```\n\nCodex searches the web and provides an answer with current information.' },
          { type: 'callout', variant: 'tip', content: 'Cached web search is the default because it\'s safer — live pages could contain prompt injection. Use live mode only when you need the latest information.' },
        ],
